[4.37422, "o", "The model has two layers, the first layer uses a ReLU activation, and the second\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> layer uses a Softmax Activation. These are the shapes of each parameter:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> W1 : (10, 784)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> b1 = (10, 1)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> W2 = (10, 10)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> b2 = (10, 1)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> Do not alter shapes in any way. \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> For some reason, my accuracy and loss are stuck. Help me diagnose.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> You have access to one npz file: gradients.npz.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - /app/gradients.npz holds the gradients for the first 100 iterations of training.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> - Once loaded, each value can be accessed as such:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - dW1 = data['\"'\"'dW1'\"'\"']\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - Shape: (iterations, 10, 784)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - dW2 = data['\"'\"'dW2'\"'\"']\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - Shape: (iterations, 10, 10)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - db1 = data['\"'\"'db1'\"'\"']\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?20"]
[4.374422, "o", "04h>   - Shape: (iterations, 10, 1)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - db2 = data['\"'\"'db2'\"'\"']\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h>   - Shape: (iterations, 10, 1)\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> You may analyze this data however you would like, but you do not have to analyze\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> the data.\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> Within the /app/fix.py file, you may have access to these functions:\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> set_forward - this allows you to recode the forward pass\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> set_inits - this allows you to recode the initialization of parameters\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> set_backward - this allows you to recode the backward pass\r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> You may choose to edit ONLY ONE of these functions. The function you rewrite \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> will be used to retrain in the new model. If you choose to not edit a function, \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?2004h> the original implementation will be used. Docstrings on how the function should \r\n\u001b[?2004l\r\u001b[?20"]
